_**This post is part of a series on the approval of the construction of
Hidroaysén hydroelectric power station. Read all about the project,[the “for”
and “against” arguments and the initial reactions when the news was
revealed.](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2011/05/16/chile-citizens-reject-
the-hidroaysen-dam-project/)**_

After the approval of the construction of the [Hidroaysén](www.hidroaysen.cl/)
hydrolectric power station in the [ Aysén
region](http://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Regi%C3%B3n_Ays%C3%A9n_del_General_Carlos_Ib%C3%A1%C3%B1ez_del_Campo)
of the Chilean Patagonia on May 9, 2011, there have been many protests around
the country.

According to radio station _[Cooperativa](http://cooperativa.cl/mas-
de-7-000-personas-llegaron-hasta-plaza-italia-a-protestar-por-
hidroaysen/prontus_nots/2011-05-09/201052.html) _[es] _:_

> The demonstrations managed to unite 7,000 people in Plaza Italia, in the
> capital Santiago […] The protests continue in cities like
> [Coyhaique](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Coihaique) -directly in front of
> the Environmental Evaluation Commission-,
> [Concepción](http://gosouthamerica.about.com/od/chisurconcepcion/p/Concepcion.htm),
> [Temuco](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Temuco),
> [Valparaíso](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Valpara%C3%ADso) and
> [Valdivia](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Valdivia), where police dispersed
> the crowd with tear gas in a protest of about 500 people.

The protests continue daily, as well as a second massive call which brought
30,000 people to the streets on May 13. The online periodical _[El
Mostrador](http://www.elmostrador.cl/noticias/pais/2011/05/14/treinta-mil-
personas-salen-a-la-calle-contra-hidroaysen-y-le-ponen-presion-a-pinera/)
_[es] commented:

> Ecological groups have marched everyday against this initiative and the
> protests will continue until May 21st, the day that the mandate will hand in
> a published account of the affairs of the project to Parliament.

Medical doctor and Twitter user, Alvaro Rivas
([@alvarorivasMD](http://twitter.com/#!/alvarorivasMD)), sent [a live link
](http://www.diarioantofagasta.cl/tus-noticias/1441)[es] of the march through
TwitCasting. With a cameraphone, he attended the peaceful demonstration and
witnessed the police repression. He even came to the aid of a woman who was
suffering a panic attack due to the tear gas thrown.

Alvaro's narrative was followed and celebrated by many, above all, because
national television was not covering the news.

[![The No to Hidroaysén protest in front of La Moneda. Santiago, Chile 13 May,
2011. Photo by Flickr user Flavio_Camus \(CC BY-NC-ND
2.0\)](https://es.globalvoicesonline.org/wp-
content/uploads/2011/05/5717877996_71c516ac25-375x210.jpg)](https://globalvoicesonline.org/?attachment_id=68082)

The No to Hidroaysén protest in front of La Moneda. Santiago, Chile 13 May,
2011. Photo by Flickr user Flavio_Camus (CC BY-NC-ND 2.0)

